</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[657,722,1878,1903]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[657,722,1878,1903]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from remaining species by the very long tibia and acute paraembolic lamina in the male palp (
<figureCitation box="[744,870,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURE 7 A ‒ D" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,578,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[148,1433,565,1905]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7 A ‒ D. Filistatoides xichu n. sp. A. Habitus dorsal, male (Holotype). B. Male bulb. C. Male palp, prolateral. D. Same, retrolateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263121/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
Figs 
<number box="[801,814,1915,1939]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" value="7.0">7</number>
C‒D
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[882,908,1915,1939]" captionStart="FIGURE 8 A ‒ J. A ‒ D" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1829,1851]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,193,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[179,1408,193,1808]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8 A ‒ J. A ‒ D. Filistatoides insignis O. P. Cambridge, from Iztapa, Santa Rosa, Guatemala. Genitalia. A. Male palp, prolateral. B. Same, retrolateral. C ‒ D. Variation of spermathecae, dorsal view. E ‒ G. Filistatoides polita Franganillo from Dos Caminos de San Luis, Santiago de Cuba. Genitalia. E. Male palp, prolateral. F. Same, retrolateral. G. Spermathecae, dorsal. H ‒ J. Filistatoides xichu n. sp. (Holotype), male palp. H. Retrolateral. I. Prolateral. J. Bulb, ventral. Abbreviations: b = receptacle base; cd = neck; r = receptacula; ue = uterus externus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263122/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
