<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="411" pageId="9" pageNumber="410" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1806,2011]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="411" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1950,1975]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Description</emphasis>
. Male (
<typeStatus box="[429,540,1950,1975]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Holotype</typeStatus>
). Carapace yellow, with lateral margins and eye area black. Eyes encircled in black. Chelicerae orange with anterior black spot. Labium and endites yellowish. Sternum white. Palp and legs yellowish, with sparse, black annulations. Abdomen dorsally cream with 
<number box="[1037,1079,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
black chevrons, laterally and ventrally white (
<figureCitation box="[336,427,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 7 A ‒ D" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,578,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[148,1433,565,1905]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7 A ‒ D. Filistatoides xichu n. sp. A. Habitus dorsal, male (Holotype). B. Male bulb. C. Male palp, prolateral. D. Same, retrolateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263121/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">
Fig. 
<number box="[389,404,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="7.0">7</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). Total length 
<number box="[591,629,188,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="2.5">2.5</number>
. Carapace length 
<number box="[830,867,188,212]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="1.7">1.7</number>
, width 1.0. PME separated by their diameter. Palp measurements: femur 
<number box="[402,437,224,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="1.1">1.1</number>
long, patella 
<number box="[594,629,224,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.4">0.4</number>
long, tibia 
<number box="[761,798,224,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.8">0.8</number>
, long, 
<number box="[876,911,224,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.3">0.3</number>
wide. Leg measurements: I femur 
<number box="[1310,1344,224,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="2.2">2.2</number>
/ patella 
<number box="[151,185,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.4">0.4</number>
/ another articles lacking; II 
<number box="[507,541,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="1.4">1.4</number>
/ 
<number box="[558,592,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.4">0.4</number>
/ 
<number box="[609,643,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="1.6">1.6</number>
/ 
<number box="[660,694,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="1.5">1.5</number>
/ 
<number box="[711,745,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.7">0.7</number>
/ 
<number box="[761,799,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="5.6">5.6</number>
; III 
<number box="[848,881,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="1.1">1.1</number>
/ 
<number box="[899,933,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.5">0.5</number>
/ 
<number box="[950,984,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.8">0.8</number>
/ 
<number box="[1000,1034,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.9">0.9</number>
/ 
<number box="[1051,1085,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.6">0.6</number>
/ 
<number box="[1102,1140,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="3.9">3.9</number>
; IV 
<number box="[1190,1224,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="1.4">1.4</number>
/ 
<number box="[1241,1275,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.7">0.7</number>
/ 1.0/ 
<number box="[1343,1377,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="1.4">1.4</number>
/ 
<number box="[1393,1427,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="0.8">0.8</number>
/ 
<number box="[151,189,296,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="9.2">9.2</number>
. Palpal tibia almost two times the length of the bulb, not enlarged in distal area (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1240,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 7 A ‒ D" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,578,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[148,1433,565,1905]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7 A ‒ D. Filistatoides xichu n. sp. A. Habitus dorsal, male (Holotype). B. Male bulb. C. Male palp, prolateral. D. Same, retrolateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263121/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">
Figs 
<number box="[1170,1184,296,319]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="7.0">7</number>
B‒D
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1253,1316,296,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 8 A ‒ J. A ‒ D" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1829,1851]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,193,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[179,1408,193,1808]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8 A ‒ J. A ‒ D. Filistatoides insignis O. P. Cambridge, from Iztapa, Santa Rosa, Guatemala. Genitalia. A. Male palp, prolateral. B. Same, retrolateral. C ‒ D. Variation of spermathecae, dorsal view. E ‒ G. Filistatoides polita Franganillo from Dos Caminos de San Luis, Santiago de Cuba. Genitalia. E. Male palp, prolateral. F. Same, retrolateral. G. Spermathecae, dorsal. H ‒ J. Filistatoides xichu n. sp. (Holotype), male palp. H. Retrolateral. I. Prolateral. J. Bulb, ventral. Abbreviations: b = receptacle base; cd = neck; r = receptacula; ue = uterus externus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263122/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">
<number box="[1253,1266,296,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="8.0">8</number>
H‒J
</figureCitation>
). Embolus sinuous with elongate ventral furrows (Fig. 
<number box="[642,673,332,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="95.0">95</number>
). Abdomen 
<number box="[810,845,332,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" value="1.5">1.5</number>
long.
</paragraph>
